definition.value: This is an AE which is an autoimmune disease characterized by the presence of elevated blood levels of a specific autoantibody, now called anti-U1 ribonucleoprotein (RNP) together with a mix of symptoms of systemic lupus erythematosus (SLE), scleroderma, and polymyositis.
This is an AE which is a type of arthritis in which there is a long-term inflammation of the joints of the spine.
This is an AE which is paralysis caused by illness or injury that results in the partial or total loss of use of all four limbs and torso; paraplegia is similar but does not affect the arms.
This is an AE which is a sleep disorder where the patient moves limbs involuntarily and periodically during sleep, and has symptoms or problems related to the movement.
This is an AE which is a stump pain of the removal of a limb by trauma, medical illness, or surgery.
This is an AE which is frequently associated with other cerebral malformations.
This is an AE which is inflammation of the tissues in the mid-chest, or mediastinum.
This is an AE which refers a consequence of diaphragm dysfunction and atrophy, is common in the ICU and associated with serious clinical consequences.
This is an AE which is a major abnormality in the shape of shoulder compared to the normal shape of that part.
This is an AE which is typically a symptom-limiting condition that resolves spontaneously.
This is an AE which is a major abnormality in the shape of neck compared to the normal shape of that part.
This is an AE which is any damage or abnormal change in the tissue of cervical plexus, usually caused by disease or trauma.
This is an AE which is a cervical root distressing feeling often caused by intense or damaging stimuli.
This is an AE which is flattening of  the vertebrae of the neck, immediately below the skull.
This is an AE which is a medical condition of pregnancy in which the cervix begins to dilate (widen) and efface (thin) before the pregnancy has reached term.
This is an AE which is a disorder in which the muscles that generate a person's voice go into periods of spasm.
This is an AE which is a group of inherited diseases whose main feature is a progressive gait disorder.
This is an AE which is a feature of altered skeletal muscle performance with a combination of paralysis, increased tendon reflex activity, and hypertonia.
This is an AE which is a highly characteristic, abnormal, sustained spasm of the facial muscles that appears to produce grinning.
This is an AE which is a behavioral characteristic assigned to those with conditions that are regarded as rare or dysfunctional such as somatic dysfunction.
This is an AE which is a mental and behavioral disorder characterized by recurring, multiple, and current, clinically significant complaints about somatic symptoms.
This is an AE which is a perception in the absence of an external stimulus that has the qualities of a real perception.
This is an AE which is a fixed belief  that is not amenable to change in light of conflicting evidence.
This is an AE which is a method of medication administration in which a medicine is injected into the epidural space around the spinal cord.
This is an AE which is a form of empyema – a collection of pus, in the subdural space.
This is an AE which refers to an effusion in the subdural space, usually of cerebrospinal fluid.
This is an AE which is postictal process of a loss of motor function in one or more muscles.
This is an AE which has a variable definition in the literature without consideration of degree or substratification of other confounders such as the presence of arthritis or pain.
This is an AE which is a disorder of viscous, non-Newtonian fluid found in the cavities of synovial joints.
This is an AE which is the medical term for inflammation of the synovial membrane.
This is an AE which is crystal of  viscous, non-Newtonian fluid found in the cavities of synovial joints.
This is an AE which is a group of diseases with necrotising whose hallmark is inflammation of subcutaneous adipose tissue (the fatty layer under the skin panniculus adiposus).
This is an AE which is a collection or gathering of pus within a naturally existing anatomical cavity.
This is an AE which is an accumulation of serous fluid in a body cavity.
This is an AE which is conditions causing chronic, often intermittent pain affecting the joints or connective tissue.
This is an AE which is an inflammatory disease that can involve the heart, joints, skin, and brain.
This is an AE which is a syndrome characterised by recurrent, self-resolving inflammatory attacks in and around the joints, consists of arthritis or periarticular soft tissue inflammation.
This is an AE which is a neurodegenerative disease that is mostly inherited.
This is an AE which is the occurrence of involuntary movements in a combination of chorea (irregular migrating contractions) and athetosis (twisting and writhing).
This is an AE which is crystal of  viscous, non-Newtonian fluid found in the cavities of synovial joints.
This is an AE which is a basal ganglia syndrome resulting from damage to the subthalamic nucleus in the basal ganglia.

This is an AE which is a medical sign consisting of the involuntary contraction of muscles, which may be caused by disorders that increase the action potential frequency of muscle cells or the nerves that innervate them.
This is an AE which is a medical condition where  local body muscles contract and relax rapidly and repeatedly, resulting in uncontrolled shaking.
This is an AE which is an involuntary, somewhat rhythmic, muscle contraction and relaxation involving oscillations or twitching movements of one or more body parts.
This is an AE which is a medical sign observed in patients with low calcium.
This is an AE which is any damage or abnormal change in the tissue of meniscus , usually caused by disease or trauma.
This is an AE which is a form of inflammatory arthritis characterized by recurrent attacks of a red, tender, hot, and swollen joint.
This is an AE which is a disorder characterized by catching or locking of the involved finger.
This is an AE which is a disorder characterized by rapid, uncoordinated jerking movements primarily affecting the face, hands and feet.
This is an AE which is a medical condition where body muscles contract and relax rapidly and repeatedly, resulting in uncontrolled shaking and is clonic.
